NAME
    emojify - Convert emoji codes to Unicode emoji

SYNOPSIS
    emojify [options] [file ...]

DESCRIPTION
    emojify is a shell script that converts emoji codes in text to their corresponding Unicode emoji characters. It can process input from files or standard input.

OPTIONS
    -h, --help      Display help information
    -v, --version   Display version information
    -l, --list      List all available emoji and their codes
    -s, --strict    Only replace emoji codes flanked by colons (:code:)
    -t, --text      Treat input as pure text (ignore markdown syntax)

USAGE
    Pipe text containing emoji codes to emojify, or use it to process files directly.

EXAMPLES
    echo "I :heart: emoji" | emojify
    emojify input.txt > output.txt
    emojify --strict < input.txt > output.txt

OUTPUT
    Text with emoji codes replaced by Unicode emoji characters.

BREAKDOWN
emojify is a shell script that uses sed or awk to perform text substitutions. It likely contains a dictionary of emoji codes and their corresponding Unicode characters. The script reads input line by line, applies the substitutions, and outputs the result.
